id: pm-mwiz
title: SDK starter example leaves extension health warning
description: "The SDK-first starter extension registered its demonstration no-op migration as active, causing a clean install to report extension_migration_pending in pm health."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[6]: audit,dogfood,extensions,health,pm-cli,sdk
created_at: "2026-04-30T19:47:34.400Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-30T20:03:36.380Z"
deadline: "2026-05-01T19:47:34.400Z"
author: codex-audit
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: Starter extension install no longer leaves pm extension doctor or pm health with a pending migration warning; targeted test covers the example migration status.
parent: pm-3fti
resolution: Changed the SDK starter example no-op migration from active/pending to applied and made run() return applied=true.
expected_result: Installing the reference SDK starter extension leaves pm extension doctor and pm health clean.
actual_result: Patched temp install reported doctor status ok and pm health ok=true with no warnings.
fixed_version: 2026.3.12-audit
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-30T19:47:34.400Z",codex-audit,"Duplicate check before create: pm search 'starter extension migration pending health warning' found closed historical migration-health work only (for example pm-42oa and pm-cw6c),no open item for the SDK starter example regression. Net-new issue is required under current audit feature pm-3fti."
  "2026-04-30T19:47:54.506Z",codex-audit,"Implemented fix: starter extension no-op migration now reports status=applied and run() returns applied=true. Added targeted test and verified patched temp install clears pm health extension warning."
